<br>
I've grouped with a monk on a couple occasions when my wife couldn't play, and I must say that a monk is almost capable of replacing a necro. There are two chief reasons. First, a monk can always pull singles, and as a mage, once I'm fighting a single mob, I've already won. Mages fall short on crowd control, but really shine at doing damage. Second, with an unlimited supply of bandages, a monk doesn't need a healer. He's got Mend, he's got the best Bind Wound skill in the game. And if those fail, he's got Feign Death.<br>
<br>
So if you're a mage and you don't have a necro handy, a monk makes a nice second choice. When you're already a mage-necro duo, go ahead and invite a monk into the group. You will never, ever stop fighting and the experience just rolls in.<br>
<br>
EDIT: Heh, now I'm a Master Summoner? This is almost as good as leveling up in Everquest. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  &quot;Wow, Elementalist was a hell level, but I soloed throughout Conjurer level and it just blew by.&quot;  <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 33rd Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unefariusgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nefarius Gnome</A> at: 10/23/00 12:42:22 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ezno</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/posticons/eyes.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 195<br> <font color=#333333>(10/24/00 4:38:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=76.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mage-Necro, Mage-Monk</span><hr size=1> <br>
I'd have to say that Mage-Necro is so powerful that its almost scary.   A necro friend of mine (lvl 53, I'm lvl 52) go to Skyfire and do constant pulls without any problems.   For fighting a single MoB I don't think you'll find a more powerful combination.   I personally can't wait for lvl 54 when we can both summon backstabbing pets.  That'll be almost freaky.<br>
<br>
However, Everquest has many different ways of playing the game.  For instance, a Necro/Magician combo is exceedingly powerful but would have trouble breaking a camp of 4+ creatures whereas a Druid could break that camp alone.   <br>
<br>
I would rate a Druid/Magician combo very high on the list.  Druids give you snare/sow/ports/heals/damage allow you to break any outdoor camp and will allow you to start 'kiting' almost immediately.    <p> <br>
